76561198281568815,Not Recommended,249650,32059308,Posted: 30 May,all,Lonewolf Enoch,"= 2017/05/30 =Here is what you get from Blackguards by Daedalic Entertainment.Linear story basedPre-made heroes (characters)Skill based characters (not class based)Spell caster or non-spell caster class (all skill available except spell type for non-spell caster, spell casters have a one time use of AP(Adventurer Points) in the beginning when creating your character)Close range weapons : Dagger, Sword/Saber, Axe/Mace, Rapier/Foil, Staves, Spears, 2-Handed Sword, 2-Handed MaceLong range weapons : Bows, Crossbows, Throwing weaponsLeft/Right hand slot : One-hand weapon + shield, Dual wield, 2-Handed wepon, or bare-fist (not recommended)Armor slots : Head, Chest, Legs, Hands, Feet, Waist (for belt to put items usable in combat)Attributes : Courage, Cleverness, Intuition, Charisma, Dexterity, Agility, Constitution, Strength, Vitality, Astral-energy(mana), Magic resistance [Each attribute points contribute to Base Values]Base Values : Vitality, Attack, Parry, Dodge, Ranged combat, Initiative, Magic resistance, Astral Energy, SpeedTalents : Body-control, Will power, Perception, Traps, Street-wise, Survival, Animal Lore, Warcraft, Treat WoundsSpecial Abilities : from Power Blow, Tripple Shot, Dual Wield, to Astral regeneration. 16 main abilities, 39 including sub-abilities (for example Dodge 1->Dodge 2-<Dodge 3)= The below is a personal review/feeling of the game, you may feel differently! =The goods1. ""The complex rule system"". All these stats doing all sorts of different things! A must for the sophisticated(?) nerdy RPGer.2. Equipment changes the character outlook (even made me use a lesser equipment just for the looks that I prefered)3. Each hero (or should I say villain) has a unique touch of personality in the story4. Graphics/Animation of skills shows the effort of the developers.The bads1. Not-so-good-working ""The complex rule system"".If I see a 60% hit chance, I expect to hit 6 times out of 10 tries, or 3 out of 5.But I miss most of the time.The game is a liar in this sense and no one likes to be lied to.2. Limited AP (Adventurer Points) to level up your characters.No random mobs. All encounters are pre-decided.3. Some encounters are almost impossible if you level-up incorrectly due to the limited AP.Makes you restart the game because you cannot go any further.So don't think of making a jack-of-all-trades bard-like character...Your frustration level will rise to max gauge.4. Receive same amount of set Experience points (or Adventure Points) for each encounter, no matter how many opponents you fell. There are some encounters where you will meet infinite (respawning) mobs. If you down 1 mob and finish the objective, it will give you the same reward as downing 100 mobs before finishing the objective.= conclusion =It almost felt like a puzzle game more than an RPG because some (if not most) encounters had specific methods to win easily. Other methods, not so easy or impossible (to me).Personally, I like to farm/grind, especially when I cannot beat a certain area but not with Blackguards.Perhaps you will survive better than me but comparing the enjoyment to the frustration level, Blackguards is not recommened."
