,Recommended,249650,10829875,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,venkman,"Really love it! This game is misunderstood very often.+ great gameplay (not as good as XCOMs but still nice)+ based on The Dark Eye - refreshing compared to all the games based on D&D+ nice story+ nice quests (and side quests)+ funny interaction in-between the characters+ really good value for money when on sale+ lots of different skills and builds to explore (a bit confusing and overwhelming for beginners though)+ good difficulty (it will be very challenging at times and you will have to change your tactics which worked before)-	Obviously not a huge development budget (they made the best out of it)-	Graphics are nice but could be way better (eg. cutscenes …)-	Skills & talents can be difficult to understand. You’ll probably need to google a bit to understand the different character values.-	Some bugs can be frustrating, eg. when the healer in-between the gladiator fights won’t heal you anymore. There aren’t many but this one made it very hard for me-	Save often. (same as xcom). It could save you time.-	Usability in the stat/spell/… screens could be better, especially when trying to figure out which weapon does more damage.All in all, I can live without the best graphics and animations (like XCOM does superb). I was willing to learn about the skills and mechanics. I accepted the couple of bugs I encountered – it only lead to the game being more difficult but didn’t break the game itself.After reading many negative reviews I think the problem is that this game isn’t like many other games out there, it’s comparable to XCOM but with possibility to skill your characters in a complex way. You can’t save every minute and decisions you made today could be a problem much later. You may have to do some side quests to get the experience to advance. You won’t be able to blindly upgrade every skill and spell there is. You will have to use different tactics. Using Takate with his piercing skill will work awesome most of the time, but if an enemy is immune to piercing you should better have given him some other weapon and skills (I learned this the hard way).Obviously something went wrong during the beta version, because most of the negative reviews are from back then. I didn’t experience many of the problems from back then. If you like turn based games with a lot of strategy involved you’ll probably like this. If you want to kill many monsters with huge firewalls better get path of exile ;)"
