,Not Recommended,249650,31238146,Posted: 19 April,all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,"Hey everyone and this is my review about the game!This is a RPG(RNG) Turn based strategy game.Interface/Menu/SettingsThere is a difficulty level settings available.You are able to toggle the tutorial.There is a master volume slidebar available and it is also % based.There is a music volume slidebar available and it is also % based.There is a effect volume slidebar available and it is also % based.There is a voice volume slidebar available and it is also % based.There are some different resolution sizes available.About the game.Before you are able to play your game, they will ask you if you do wish to be a Mage, Hunter or a warrior. Each class has their own advantage and disadvantage. This game is borderline... Well let's say uncreative. You click on a map location and that level will start. You are either fighting against an enemy or you are in a town. Once in a town you are able to buy/sell items at a shop, Rest to recover the stats, Talk to some people or even doing quest activities. Whenever you are fighting against an enemy the combat rules are pretty simple (It's like Heroes of might and magic). The battlefield is on a Grid and each unit take turns for their action. The character speed is known as ""initiative"" and the higher number, the faster a character is able to perform again in a battle. Sadly enough the game suffers from ""Random number generator"" in fights (Such as X-Com) which means, Even if you have a 95% attack chance against an enemy. Well jokes on you, The 95% is not really 95% as you are still missing pretty often. Your character is able to level up and they are able to learn new spells, talents and other things. They can be equipped with items to make them stronger in battles.Subtitles are voiced over. You are able to skip and fastforward it.Great Graphics.Turn based Combat.Decent story.Random number generated % based in battles.Character has some customiziation.There is a rules control overview.Alot of ingame tips/explainations.It has dialogues and cutscenes.Other things.The random number generator in turn based games is simply NOT WORKING and will always ruin the game. Xcom is a good example (MY OPINION) as the enemy always have a higher hit chance than you will ever get.So in short words. ""Combat mechanic is unfair towards the player as it is happening too often""-------------------I Give this game a 5/10"
