76561198115374089,Recommended,249650,12943874,"Posted: 14 November, 2014",all,SkarabCZ,"Graphics: 7/10Music: 7/10Animations: 6/10Story: 8/10Humour: 8/10Replayability: 9/10Naurim's voice acting: 11/10I'm so glad I bought this game even though it had rather mediocre reviews on Steam (don't know rly why).Blackguards is a turn-based RPG taking place in Aventuria world (Dark Eye franchise) where the main protagonist is accused of murder and must find a way how to redeem himself.I have played 80 hours so far and still have not finished the game (which is huge).. but I must admit I rerolled my main character couple of times just to try out new skills/approaches. :)I love the story. I love the quests. I love the in-game humour - I dare to say the humour is even better than in Borderlands 2. It's not so forced and it's generally cooler. :DYou lead your party of loveable outlaws throughout a dangerous world and you are balancing on a narrow edge of legal and illegal behavior. Don't expect any clichés. These guys are not your normal do-gooders, but you will love them. :DChapter 1 and 2 are very linear but that changes in Chapter 3 which is huge and has lots of side quests. The game can be  (sometimes) pretty difficult even on normal difficulty and you WILL have to use your brain (or Google). :DThe game is not likely worth the full price (39.99 EUR) which is a bit overpriced but I would definitely recommend buying it for 15-20 EUR on sale. You will spend hours and hours playing it.Even though there are only 3 classes in Normal game mode to pick, you can always switch to Expert game mode and create a new game and a hero from scratch.You will be able to create your champion as a mix of warrior/mage/hunter with emphasis on various skills/abilities and talents of your liking.If you like turn-based RPG's or strategies with a good story, I highly recommend you buying this game."
