76561197986964932,Recommended,249650,11166663,"Posted: 10 July, 2014",all,Bad Alchemy,"Bloody brilliant. There are some seriously bizzare negative comments on this game but let me clarify some points.1. Does it have a plot? Yes. Is it linear? Yes. Does it matter? Not really.2. Is the interface aweful? No not in the slightest, you can choose between a right click menu or a standard button bar.3. Is it full of bugs? No, the bugs like the character inventory head and feet images in the wrong place has been fixed.4. Is the character creation and character sheet bad? No, actually its very good. You spend 10-15 mins reading everything and realise there is so much death there are lots of replay options to have a different game. Its essentially D&D stats. Played Baldurs Gate, Diablo or any other game like that and its simple, intuitive and in this case, very good.5. Its all combat, is this bad? Not really, I enjoy limited dialogue and lots of fighting. Baldurs Gate 1&2 are mostly this and they are cult classics. How good was The Banner Saga, I mean we all loved the talking but the hexed passed fighting where was it all was. This is that game on steriods.6. Is the fact the game based on a roleplay system a problem? No its actually its strength as it has lots of depth. You can turn the battle log to simple mode if you like or you can have the log go mad with the dice rolling detail. (I turn it off).Its a damn fine enjoyable game, the fact the scenery is a part of the game (Giant birds dropping rocks, crates being knocked over, tenticles from a monster breaking walkways, oil being set on fire, slippery mud, quicksand and bogs) makes this an awesome and unique experience."
