76561198019788935,Recommended,249650,9050277,"Posted: 10 February, 2014",all,chrishax,"Like Might and Magic X Legacy, this title is going to polarise opinion madly. Both are old-school turn based rpgs with more of a focus on tactics than on roleplay, and the ambition of this title is to feel like a real-life in-person, yes-there-really-is-a-live-DM kind of excperience, at which this game is mostly successful.The writing is adult, the tactics are tough, and the game has the sort of arbitrary cruelty and imperfection you get from a DMs interpretation of the rules. This is not a fps or action game, in any way, its a game for reflection. And yes its a pity there are a few genuine bugs.This game will appeal to fans of HoMM, Disciples, XCom turnbased, Badurs Gate turn based, and as I say to players of IRL RPGs. I would say right now that I prefer MMX - Legacy to this, and its kinda stoopid that both games came on within a few weeks, given that its 5 years since the last half-decent rpg.But if you're the kind of person above, then this is a truly excellent title, and you should buy both !!! Don't be put off by some of the reviews that score it for what it isnt...."
