76561198033473318,Not Recommended,249650,9219425,"Posted: 22 February, 2014",all,Mikolaj,"Many games call themselves ""tactical rpgs"" but that's just a slogan. This one really is. If you love turn based combat, with simple to learn rules but a lot of nuances, if losing a fight makes you want to play it better - this is a game for you. The story is simple but not bad, it progresses through dialogues as there is no actual exploration. But the whole point is developing your party and fighting cleverly designed fights. They require you to use terrain, positioning, traps and other tricks to survive. If by RPG you understand a game where you just click on an opponent - this game is not for you. Actually I would rather recommend this game to a strategy fan not an RPG one.EDIT> I am sad but I feel I have to change my recommendation to a negative one. While the game itself is great, I ran into a bug in a fight at the end of chapter 3. Basically the turn of one of AI characters (Manolo) never ends. Thus I can't complete this fight and progress with the game. I reported the bug 3 months ago and still nothing, only a generic automated response."
