,Not Recommended,249650,28982585,Posted: 3 January,all,Crazyi,"I have mixed feelings on this game. I got it on sale and would recommend it as such, but this game is not worth 40$.Nothing in this game is bad except for the UI, but nothing is good either. Nothing impressed me at all. The spell system having 3 stats associated to every spell just doesn't make sense. I need strength for magic? Wait what? Okay it would make sense if its a force push or something maybe that fits right? Well one of them creates and arcane wall, the other is a debuff. How is that associated to strength at all?Most irritating part is some fights are just not properly balanced. There is one fight I spent over an hour on, had the moves mapped to a science, and just needed the RNG to connect. If you let the guy hit you on the second turn and poison you, you simply cannot win. So one companion has to move the perfect amount of tiles away from the enemy so it will chase him, while the other moves away and shoots at the non poisoning opponent. Kiting of this level doesn't have a place in a game like this. When I have to take my tank and run him in circles to not die, I feel like the developers missed something...  And to put it in perspective, I have the best armor and stats possible at the current place for a tank, and he cannot tank nor do I even consider him ""tanky"". Your shield will add a lot to your parry, but you can only parry once per turn turn so what is the point? My mage honestly has just as good of a chance to survive as he does wearing cloth without a shield.I love games like this, and this one just doesn't shine enough for me to recommend it over what is out there. As I said I don't feel it is bad, but I am not finishing the game."
76561198045512003,Recommended,249650,29990692,Posted: 17 February,all,peddroelm,"Another example of a great (in places) game putting off players do to poor presentation of core game mechanics to player base / very poor ingame feedback.I don't know what the developers were aiming for with the way the final product turned out (it is NOT due to technical ineptitude or lack of creative ability - the game mechanics are consistent with its defined rule set, full of intelligent puzzles and reasonably bug free).The lack of transparency (markedly unsound - it badly hurts their sales numbers by quickly alienating the ""shallower"" player base. ) seems to be caused largely due to intended design. Maybe TDE (dark eye) game rules are were so second nature to the developers they coudn't see how difficult it will be for ""foreigners"" to make sense of their otherwise ""working within parameters"" product.It almost like the game is made by aliens strangers to earth based game interface progression in the last 20 years. Maybe this what a game made by programmers/designers that don't play computer games should be expected to turn out (speculation).cons-very limited ruleset/mecanics exposition and ingame feedback (steam guides mostly fixes this)-alien game interface: bits of relevant information are scattered all over the place (need to navigate 5-6 ""screens"" to gather basic info about a character - a feat the good modern games can achieve in 1-2 ""screens"" with overwelmingly superior amount of detail - wastes player time, hurts immersion)-stoneage like combat log functionality (mising a lot game critical events and the ones presented lack detail)-rough spell/ weapon class balance-nearly impossible to read opponent's percentage based resists ( some even have vulnerabilities to certain damage types but it is extremely hard to tell due to the hidden resist stats , RNG damage component and poor combat log features)-liniar story, set drops(limited itemisation issues) and poor spell/abilities balance (few powerbuilds builds) leads to poor replayability value. (maybe the obfuscation was intended to mask/hide the poor balance to the players - or the poor balance is the result of the obfuscation making it hard for the devs to see the problems ?)pros-the community with a bit of help from developers managed to unwind most of the critical game mechanics (check out the game's player guides section)-the game is well oiled (very few bugs), the creative people did great - very high intelligent puzzle combat variation(enjoyable once you start grasping the game mechanics).I still recommend this game despite its numerous flaws because it has the capability to enthral players for hours, but wait for significant special offer discounts ."
76561197971765720,Not Recommended,249650,29793030,Posted: 8 February,all,Pelius,"I want to like this game, I really do. But there are several critical issues that the game designers should have fixed before release or fixed in a patch.The most critical issue is there are points in the game that are dead ends. What I mean by this is there are situations that will force you to restart because you won’t be able to get around them. One example is a scenario where your players cant leave a series of encounters and if you can’t beat the one of those encounters the game is effectively over. Scratch 15 hours of play. I assume there are more to come.The game looks great and the system is deep enough to make it interesting. The issue is with the encounter design and the above is only one example (although be it the worst) so far in my playthrough."
