,Not Recommended,249650,13234092,"Posted: 4 December, 2014",all,chezwizard,"TLDR -- A lot of good ideas, but iffy execution.I used to recommend this game, as I really liked it. After I got it, I played through several times, and despite some overly complex -- and not well explained -- aspects, it was a (mostly) fun game. I especially liked the humor, the fact that there wasn't always a clear ""good"" choice, and that even when there was, it wasn't always mechanically superior -- i.e. better rewards for being ""good"". It was refreshingly muddy on morality.But, recently, I'd seen some comments online referencing ""crashes"" being the reason people stopped playing. So I just played through again -- and it crashed a half dozen times in my playthrough. I still enjoyed going back through this game, but I had the benefit of already understanding the confusing character sheet and knowing how to budget my xp and  money well -- what to buy and when.I think it's more than likely that most people who ran into the random -- and seemingly non-reproducible -- crashes I did won't get very far, especially with all the other aggravating factors.If you can get past the crashes, and remember to diversify the party, while focusing each character, you can have a lot of fun with it. But if you want a quick dive in for fun, go elseware."
